en_196603_0	Dambulla Police arrested 10 persons who behaved in an unruly manner during the ODI match between Sri Lanka and South Africa at the Dambulla International Cricket Stadium last night.
en_196603_1	Police said a security guard who was on duty at the vehicle park and UNP Central Provincial Councillor Tissa Bandara Herath who received injuries were admitted to Dambulla Hospital.
en_196603_2	The injured security guard, Chaminda Pushpakumara told us that one of the spectators attacked him with a glass bottle.
en_196603_3	Later, the riot police arrested the attacker.
en_196603_4	Central Provincial Councilor, Tissa Bandara Herath said that he was also assaulted when he had intervened to settle the dispute.
